    <id>http://pelupessy.github.io/blog/2017/12/23/wagyu</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><strong>英語で</strong> Outside of Japan there are some rumours on the luxurious treatment of cows before they get cut into <em>wagyu</em> beef, varying from daily massages to a special diet which includes <em>nihonshu</em>. Whether or not these rumours are true, the resulting meat is rather special, ideal for <em>yakiniku</em> (fried meat).</p>

<p><strong>Japanese:</strong> 和牛の焼肉！学生にもらいました。</p>

<p><a href="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-zKvk9Sm/0/2897d341/X3/i-zKvk9Sm-X3.jpg"><img class="center" src="https://photos.smugmug.com/photos/i-zKvk9Sm/0/2897d341/XL/i-zKvk9Sm-XL.jpg"></a></p>

